==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Three-port
<hw>Three"-port`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having three ports; specif.:
Designating a type of two-cycle internal-combustion engine in which the
mixture enters the crank case through a port uncovered by the piston
near the end of its stroke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

